<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Lodges Strong Protest Against Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of External
Affairs summoned the Pakistani Deputy High Commissioner Wednesday
evening and lodged a strong protest, deploring the "blatant and
gross violation of the privacy and sanctity of the residential
premises of the Indian diplomats."
</P>
<P>
A press release said that the Ministry demanded that measures
be taken to ensure that there are no repetitions of such incidents
in future and sought adequate security for all personnel of the
High Commission of India in Islamabad and their residential
premises.
</P>
<P>
The residential premises of two Indian diplomats based in
Islamabad, Shri Vipin Handa, Counselor and Gp. Capt. S.K. Jayaswal,
Air Adviser, were intruded upon by the operatives of the Pakistan
intelligence agencies Wednesday, it said.
</P>
<P>
These incidents follow a pattern of calibrated and escalating
harassment and brazen intimidation by Pakistani authorities of
members of the High Commission of India, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
