<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uzbekistan, China Exchange Instruments of Ratification of Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Uzbekistan and China exchanged
instruments of ratification of an extradition treaty on Wednesday
in the Uzbek capital of Tashkent, the Chinese embassy in Tashkent
told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The treaty, signed in Beijing in November 1999, was approved
respectively by the Uzbek and Chinese parliaments in February and
July this year.
</P>
<P>
The treaty will enter into force on September 29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
