<DOCNO> XIE20000831.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SOD Tomato Tried in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The Haci Group signed an
agreement with Shanghai today to grow, in large amounts, a new
variety of tomato, believed to be the first generation of bio-
engineered farm produce in China.
</P>
<P>
The new variety, called SOD tomato, was co-developed by the
Haci Group and the Chinese Agriculture University. It is pollution-
free and a dietetic.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, the Haci Group will grow SOD
tomatoes in the form of a franchise on 40 hectares of land in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Yi Ying Huan, an agriculture expert, said SOD is a kind of
erythrocuprein, which will improve one's looks and prevent aging
and clear out impurities from the body.
</P>
<P>
To date, the group has built a SOD production base in Shouguang
of east China's Shandong Province. Other provinces including
Jiangsu, Shandong, Henan and Zhejiang are negotiating with the
group to produce SOD tomatoes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
