<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, August 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- One of Israel Defense Forces' top officers resigned
Thursday in the wake of the botched operation last Saturday in
which three Israeli solders were killed by their comrades.
</P>
<P>
Shlomo Oren, the commander of Judea and Samaria (the traditional
Jewish appellation of the West Bank) Brigade, told Israel Radio
that he decided to step down to assume the responsibility for the
operation mishap. However, it is still unclear whether his
resignation had been accepted. (Israel-Operation Mishap)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Israeli soldiers shot and wounded a Lebanese youth at
the border flashpoint of Fatma Gate Thursday afternoon, security
source said.
</P>
<P>
Aly Fakhreddine, 20, was shot in the foot after hurling stones
at an Israeli army outpost across the barbed wire fence separating
Israel and Lebanon. He has been sent to near hospital. (Lebanon-
Border Clash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- The Cyprus cabinet on Thursday approved the 2001
state budget, which projects 2,417.0 million Cyprus pounds (4,834.0
million U.S. dollars) in expenditure and 1,576.0 million pounds (3,
152 million dollars) in revenue.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after a two-hour cabinet meeting, Finance Minister
Takis Clerides expressed his satisfaction with the performance of
Cyprus economy in 2000, and predicted "encouraging prospects for
2001" with an estimated rate of growth at 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The budget deficit is estimated at 841.0 million pounds (1,682.0
million dollars). (Cyprus-State Budget)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Visiting British Minister of State for Foreign Affairs
Peter Hain said here Thursday that his country will support the
peace process on the Palestinian-Israeli track until a final
solution is attained.
</P>
<P>
Hain made the pledge at a joint press conference with
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat after their talks on the latest
developments of the Middle East peace process, and the Arab and
international efforts to push the process forward. (Palestine-UK-
Peace Process) 
</P>
</TEXT>
