<HEADLINE> Argentine President Begins Five Nation Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President
Fernando De la Rua left here Thursday for Brazil as part of a tour,
which will also take him to Mexico, the United States, Canada and
China.
</P>
<P>
De la Rua will participate in Brazilia at the First South
American Summit, in which 12 leaders will examine the regional
integration, Southern Common Market (Mercosur) and the situation
in Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The leaders will discuss the strengthening of regional
democracy, trade integration, infrastructure, fighting drug
trafficking and exchanging in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they will participate in celebrations of the 500
anniversary of discovery of Brazil.
</P>
<P>
De la Rua will go back to Buenos Aires, Argentina, and on
September 4 travel to Mexico, where he will stay until September 5
and meet his counterpart Ernesto Zedillo.
</P>
<P>
From September 6 to 8, Del la Rua will visit the United States,
where he will attend the Millenium Summit of the United Nations in
New York and hold talks with U.S. President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by a plentiful entrepreneurial committee, De la Rua
will arrive in Ottawa, Canada, on September 8 for a two-day visit,
and from September 10 to 14 he will pay an official visit to China.
</P>
<P>
While in Canada and China, De la Rua will promote trade and
investment orientation toward Argentina. 
</P>
