<HEADLINE> Greece to Send More Soldiers to Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Greece has decided to send more
soldiers to the Yugoslav province of Kosovo in order to increase
the strength of the Greek military contingent serving in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Confirming this at a press briefing Thursday, Greek government
spokesman Dimitris Reppas said that Greece will send another
infantry unit to Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The new Greek battalion, which is now based in the northern
Greek city of Thessaloniki, will be stationed in the new
installations of the Rigas Fereos army camp near Urosevac.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Greece has a strong battalion of 1,200 men
participating in the NATO-led multinational peacekeeping force in
Kosovo, and most of the Greek soldiers have been stationed in the
southern part of Kosovo. 
