<HEADLINE> Xinhua Asia-Pacific Economic News Summary, Thursday, August 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA -- Statistics show that 185,000 people from home and
abroad visited Tibet Autonomous Region in the first half of the
year, an increase of 57 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas visitors rose by 40 percent to reach 35,
000 in the six-month period.
</P>
<P>
Local tourism department predicted that Tibet will become one
of the top choices of worldwide travelers in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Sources from local tourism department attributed the increase
in visitors to the facts that Chinese people now have more
holidays, which enable them to visit places as far away as Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Opening up of the region is cited as another factor which
attracts more and more overseas travelers. The Potala Palace once
received some 600 visitors daily.
</P>
<P>
In Lhasa, Xigaze and Shannan, visitors have to live at the
homes of local residents because local hotels are booked out.
</P>
<P>
Tibet boasts rich tourism resources which include 50 mountains
with an elevation of over 7,000 meters, seven peaks which are more
than 8,000 meters high, the Yarlung Zangbo River valley, the
longest in the world, colorful landforms and special wildlife
resources. The region also has typical traditional culture, the
Potala Palace and several hundred temples and monasteries.
</P>
<P>
The Potala Palace has been included in the World Culture
Heritage list, and the Johkang Monastery in Lhasa is applying to
be included in the list.
</P>
<P>
At present, Tibet is constructing eight tourism routes which
will connect Lhasa and other major cities in Tibet with
neighboring Sichuan, Yunnan and Qinghai provinces and Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region, and also with neighboring Nepal.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
LANZHOU -- The 12th Western China Commodities Trade Fair will
be held from September 2-6 in Tianshui City of Gansu Province,
northwest China.
</P>
<P>
More than 10,000 people are expected to attend the upcoming
fair, said Zhang Jinliang, mayor of Tianshui, adding that the
transaction volume is predicted at six billion yuan (about 723
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Tianshui is known as the birthplace of Fuxi, one of China's
legendary rulers credited with introduction of hunting, farming
and fishing, and of the Fuxi Culture.
</P>
<P>
Fuxi Culture Tourism Festival will be held simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
The fair is an annual event sponsored by 11 prefectures and
cities in western China and the five western railway sub-bureaus
of Xi'an, Lanzhou, Chengdu, Ankang and Yinchuan.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
LANZHOU -- The 2000 China Lanzhou Investment and Trade Fair
concluded Wednesday in Lanzhou, capital of northwest China's Gansu
Province.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizers, business turnover during the five-
day event reached 1.12 billion yuan (135 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Initial statistics show that 226 contracts worth 8.87 billion
yuan were signed during the Fair. The Fair also generated 290
million U.S. dollars in foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 enterprises from 15 provinces, autonomous regions
and municipalities attended the Fair.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou Investment and Trade Fair has been held
successfully for seven years since 1992.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
GUANGZHOU -- Guangdong Province in south China will hold a
series of events in Europe in September to try and attract foreign
funds and strengthen economic ties with European countries.
</P>
<P>
The 2000 Guangdong (Europe) Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation Trade Talks will be the largest of its kind ever held
by Guangdong in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The province will invite foreign business people to invest in
infrastructure facilities, agriculture, textiles, food, building
material industries, medicine, tourism and information sectors.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong will sponsor trade talks in Paris from September 19-
21 and an investment fair in Milan, Italy, on September 14.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE -- Singapore registered 706,318 tourist arrivals in
July 2000, the highest ever for any month in history and up 12.2
percent compared with the same period of last year, Singapore
Tourism Board said in a press release Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The increase came after two months of single-digit growth and
was led by Africa which grew by 13.9 percent, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Visitorship from all other continents also registered strong
growth with the Americas growing by 13.5 percent, Asia 12.9
percent and Oceania and Europe 8 percent and 7.8 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Of Singapore's 12 largest visitor-generating markets, seven
posted historical high tourist arrival figures for the month of
July and they are Australia, China, the United Kingdom, the United
States, South Korea, Hong Kong and India.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Singapore's tourism receipts for the first half of
this year were estimated at 5.4 billion Singapore dollars (about 3.
2 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG -- Bank of China (BOC) Group registered the pre-tax
profits of 4.8 billion HK dollars (615 million U.S. dollars) in
its commercial banking business in the first half of 2000, a
growth of 58.3 percent compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Net interest income rose by 560 million HK dollars (71.8
million U.S. dollars), representing an increase of 7.3 percent
over the same period of 1999, said Liu Jinbao, chief executive of
the BOC Hong Kong-Macao Regional Office, when he announced the
group's 2000 Interim Results here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the increase mainly to the strengthening of both
the asset and liability management, as well as fund management.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the buoyant stock market, the BOC group also got an
increase of 121 percent in brokerage income over the same period
of last year, he said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, total deposits stood at 658.5 billion HK
dollars (84.4 billion U.S. dollars), a rise of 4.5 percent over
June, 1999 and a growth of 2.9 percent compared with the end of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Loans and advances of the group totaled 355.5 billion HK
dollars (45.6 billion U.S. dollars), basically the same as those
of the corresponding period of 1999, but a slight growth of 0.6
percent from the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The loan to deposit ratio was 54 percent at end-June, a
reduction of 1.2 percentage points compared with the end of 1999,
Liu said, adding that this was due mainly to the group's higher
deposits growth rate than that of loans, in addition to the
constraints of the still sluggish credit market.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Eleven more state-owned enterprises of four
ministries in Myanmar will be sold through competitive bidding,
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises to be auctioned include one plot and two
warehouses of the Ministry of Hotels and Tourism, six cinemas of
the Ministry of Information, one timber shop of the Ministry of
Forestry and one ice factory of the Ministry of Livestock and
Fishery.
</P>
<P>
These enterprises are respectively located in nine townships of
the country -- Danubyu, Lanmadaw, Mongywa, Pyin Oo Lwin, Taunggyi,
Myingyan, Hinthada, Mandalay and Ye, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been implementing a privatization plan for its
state-owned economic enterprises (SEEs) since January 1995, aimed
at systematically transferring them into effective business
organizations.
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Laos' Gross Domestic Product (GDP)increased 5.9% in
the first 10 months of the current fiscal year to be ended on
September 30, on a year-on-year basis, surpassing the official
target of 5%, said a report reaching here Thursday from the
official Laos News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The data was presented at a monthly meeting of the Lao
government late August, under the chairmanship of Prime Minister
Sisavath Keobounphanh, it said.
</P>
<P>
The growth rates in the main GDP sectors of agricultural and
forestry, industry and handicraft, and services during the first
10 months were 4.4%, 7.3% and 6.4%, respectively, it stated.
</P>
<P>
CHENGDU -- A Chinese company in western Sichuan Province made
major breakthroughs in developing routing switch products, the
most essential equipment in internet technology.
</P>
<P>
Proved to be on par with international standards, this Chinese-
made products is expected to pose a challenge to the U.S.-based
Sisco which currently holds monopoly of China's routing switch
market.
</P>
<P>
Maipu Information Technology Group, based in the capital city
of Chengdu, told reporters that it will realize the
industrialization of routing switch production and compete with
Sisco in three to five years.
</P>
<P>
So far, Maipu's routing switches were already successfully
applied to some financial, public security and postal departments
in China.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
QINHUANGDAO -- Qinhuangdao, a port city in north China's Hebei
Province, has become the largest international distribution and
transfer center for fruits in north China, according to Mayor Ning
Jinbiao.
</P>
<P>
According to Ning, fresh fruits are transported via the
Qinhuangdao Port from Americas and Southeast Asia to Mongolia,
Russia, Middle Asia and central and western parts of China, and
vice versa.
</P>
<P>
The city is also the country's largest banana distributing hub.
"In 1999, Qinhuangdao imported 240,000 tons of bananas, accounting
for 52 percent of the country's total," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Qinhuangdao, 278 kilometers east of Beijing, is also a major
grain importer in China. "The corn exports stood at 1 million tons
last year, ranking second in China," he said.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, China plans to build Qinhuangdao Port into a big
trading and transport center for minerals and other industrial
materials, according to the mayor.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SHENZHEN -- About 64 percent of the overseas-financed
businesses in Shenzhen City, in south China's Guangdong Province,
have reported making profits.
</P>
<P>
Information from an annual checkup by a group of seven
governmental departments said that 7,464 operational overseas-
backed businesses made a combined profit of 17.5 billion yuan in
1999, up 20 percent from 1998.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1999, Shenzhen approved 11,744 overseas-backed
businesses and more than 20 billion U.S. dollars of overseas
capital were invested in the city.
</P>
<P>
The 7,464 overseas businesses earned 251.4 billion yuan in
sales last year, paid 7.6 billion yuan in state taxes, and
employed 1.16 million people.
</P>
<P>
While improving services for overseas investors, local
administrative departments have been giving a helping hand to
investors in difficult situations, which has helped create a
favorable production and operation environment.
</P>
<P>
The efforts have paid off. Overseas investors' confidence in
Shenzhen has led to increased investment in the city.
</P>
<P>
In 1999 alone, 355 overseas financed businesses increased
investments, with the added volume amounting to 630 million U.S.
dollars.
</P>
