<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolian President to Visit Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- President Nachagyn Bagabandy of
Mongolia will arrive here Friday for a four-day state visit to the
Philippines, the first-ever by a Mongolian leader, the Philippine
government said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Undersecretary Lauro Baja of the Department of Foreign Affairs
said the visit of President Bagabandy is in line with the
Philippines policy "to maintain friendly relations with almost all
states."
</P>
<P>
Baja said in a statement that the visit should "spur closer
cooperation between the Philippines and Mongolia."
</P>
<P>
President Bagabandy is scheduled to arrive here Friday
afternoon and he will call on Philippine President Joseph Estrada
at the Presidential Palace shortly after his arrival, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents will witness the signing of bilateral
agreements between the Philippines and Mongolia on air services,
investments,culture and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
President Bagabandy will also meet with officials of the Asian
Development Bank and the World Health Organization's Western
Pacific Regional Office in Manila before flying home on September
4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
