<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed lower on
Singapore Stock Market Thursday as the benchmark Straits Times
Index (STI) shed 17.57 points to end at 2,147.77 in marginal
trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume shrank to 87.91 million units worth 184.68
million Singapore dollars (108 million U.S. dollars). Despite the
downward STI, gainers still led losers by 120 to 103 with 347
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was a 12.99 million parcel by ITech Grp which
was transacted at 0.35 Singapore dollars per share. It was
followed by ST Engg which had 9.71 million shares done. Medi-Ring
was the next with 4.92 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Goodwood led gainers of the day, surging up 100 cents to close
at 27 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 moved up 40 cents to finish
at 36.9 Singapore dollars. PacCent inched up 30 cents to end at 23.
3 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venture headed the descent of the day, giving up 70 cents to
close at 22 Singapore dollars. Chartered shed 60 cents to finish
at 14.4 Singapore dollars and SPH 100 slid by 40 cents to end at
27.5 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
