the tournaments by winning the 5,000 meters with 15:58.83. She won
the 1,500 meters on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese female runners also won the 800 meters and 400 meters
hurdles. Li Na won the 800 meters with 2:03.46 and Song Yinglan
won the 400 meters hurdles with 57.73.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka female runner Darsha Damayanthi also won her second
gold medal Thursday by winning the 200 meters with 22.84 seconds.
She won the 400 meters on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Iran grabbed its first gold at the championships thanks to men'
s 800 meters athlete Mehdi Jeloodar Zadeh. He won the event with 1:
49.80.
</P>
<P>
Oman and Syria also grabbed their first medal at the
championships. Syrian athlete Zaherfal Den Najem won the men's 400
meters huddles bronze and Mohammed al Hooti of Oman took third
place in the men's 200 meters final.
</P>
<P>
With no Asian record shattered in the championships, athletes
from China, Sri Lanka, India, Thailand and Saudi Arabia broke
seven championships records and Japanese athlete Takayo Kondo
equalled the women's pole vault Asian championships record.
</P>
<P>
The venue of the 14th Asian Track and Field Championships will
be decided during the Asian Amateur Athletic Association Congress
here on Friday. The congress also will elect new president of the
association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
