<HEADLINE> China Builds Large Software Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A large export-oriented software
industrial park has been established in Ningbo, a major port city
in east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The Tuopu International Software Park, located in the Ningbo
Bonded Zone, is co-funded by the zone and the Tuopu Group, one of
China's leading software manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
According to a development plan, 10 to 15 large software
enterprises will be established in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
Overseas software producers and Chinese students studying
abroad are encouraged to start businesses in the park, according
to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo Mayor Zhang Weiwen said at the inauguration ceremony
that besides being a production base, the park will also become a
center for training software professionals and demonstrating
software products.
</P>
<P>
A series of preferential policies, including tax breaks and
easy loans, have already been put into effect to attract investors
to the park. 
</P>
