<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoon Prapiroon Kills Four People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were killed,
and more than 80 were injured, as a result of Typhoon Prapiroon,
when it hit northern part of Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
 According to preliminary statistics, Prapiroon has caused
heavy flooding, submerged 363,933 hectares of farmland and toppled
7,538 houses in Jiangsu. The farmlands were soaked with 80
centimeters of water.
</P>
<P>
There were rainstorms for 24 hours, ending at 5 a.m. today.
Xiangshui County received a 821 millimeters of precipitation, a
record in the history of Jiangsu. The water level of some coastal
rivers surpassed the warning line by 50-100 centimeters. More than
13,800 residents of Xiangshui County have been evacuated.
</P>
<P>
Party and government leaders headed by Hui Liangyu, secretary of
the provincial committee of the Communist Party of China, rushed
to the affected areas to organize rescue efforts.
</P>
<P>
Shiliang Reservoir has opened the flood-relief channels to
lower the water level. Yancheng has allocated 30,000 life jackets,
40 electric pumps and 200,000 straw bags and sent 400 soldiers and
militiamen to fight the flood. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
