<HEADLINE> Mayor's Son Feared Kidnapped in S. Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Police investigators
are digging into reports that a son of a municipal mayor in the
southern Sulu province was abducted in Zamboanga City before dawn
Thursday,said a report of the ABS-CBN television.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations revealed Abdul Aziz Tulawi, son of
Talipao mayor Tambrin Tulawi was forcibly taken by at least six
unidentified men at a restaurant near the Zamboanga International
Airport at around 4 a.m., the TV report said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted witnesses as saying that the suspects and
their captive boarded a taxi and sped to an undisclosed area.
</P>
<P>
Sulu governor Abdusakur Tan claimed he received the same
preliminary details of the alleged kidnapping incident.
</P>
<P>
"I have information the mayor's son was last seen at 4:40 a.m.
Thursday at a village restaurant," Tan said, adding that the
victim lives at the mayor's residence.
</P>
<P>
The victim's sister, Shalima revealed, her brother had a row
with a group of unidentified men in another disco house downtown
about three weeks ago. She said she believes the same group is
behind her brother's abduction.
</P>
<P>
Tan said he has ordered Philippine National Police Sulu chief
Candido Casimiro to check on reports of the alleged abduction.
</P>
<P>
The TV report said that defense secretary Orlando Mercado was
already informed of the report and has asked the military for
verification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
