<HEADLINE> Explosion Injures 13 in S. Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen people were injured in
an explosion in the southern Philippines Thursday afternoon, the
ABS-CBN television said in a report.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, a bomb made of five mortar shells
exploded at around 4:50 p.m. outside a bus terminal in Kabacan
town of Cotabato province.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Kabacan police chief Jimmy Nabit as saying
that 13 people were injured in the blast. He said the victims have
been sent to nearby hospitals and one of them was in serious
condition.
</P>
<P>
Nabit noted that he suspected the separatist Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) was behind the blast which came after six
other bombings in Kabacan this year.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday, MILF guerrillas ambushed a group of soldiers
near the town of Matanog, killing one and wounding nine others.
</P>
<P>
The MILF leadership has called for a "holy war" against
government forces following a military campaign in Mindanao which
resulted in the falling of most of the rebel's camps.
</P>
<P>
The 15,000-strong MILF has been fighting for an independent
state in Mindanao for more than two decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
