<HEADLINE> Armstrong Bruised in Bike-Car Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Two-time Tour de France
champion Lance Armstrong suffered minor injuries when they were
struck by a car near Nice, France, local reports said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong's bicycle was destroyed and his helmet was shattered,
but he suffered only bruises to his back. He returned home after x-
rays at a local hospital showed no broken bones.
</P>
<P>
His Olympic road cycling teammate Tyler Hamilton suffered
bruises to his elbows and knees, and he also returned home.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong and Hamilton, along with US Postal Service teammate
Frankie Andreu, were descending a hill when an on-coming car
missed a turn. Andreu avoided the car, but it hit Armstrong and
Hamilton head-on.
</P>
<P>
Armstrong and Hamilton will compete in the road race and time
trial in the Olympic Games next month. 
</P>
