<HEADLINE> Zelezny Aims for Golden Treble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PRAGUE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Despite of his injury, Czech Jan
Zelezny is aiming for a javelin golden treble at the Sydney
Olympics next month.
</P>
<P>
World record-holder Zelezny, who took gold in Atlanta and
Barcelona, told reporters on Thursday before leaving for Brisbane
that he suffered a nagging rib injury.
</P>
<P>
"At the last (examination), doctors could not believe I am
throwing 90 meters while I could successully apply for a pension
as an invalid," said the 34-year-old who will compete in Sydney
even if the pain does not go away.
</P>
<P>
Zelezny has won the world championship twice and lost out on
gold in his first Olympic Games in Seoul by just 16 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
He said there was no clear-cut favourite in the event, which
starts on September 23, and his main rival will be his own
physical condition.  
</P>
