Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee in
the Macao Special Administrative Zone concluded their 5-day
inspection tour of southwest China's Guizhou Province and left for
Macao today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation headed by Wang Qiren, director of the Liaison
Office of the Central People's Government in the Macao SAR, came
to Guizhou to keep abreast of the development of State-owned
enterprises and the economic, educational and tourism development
in areas inhabited by ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Guizhou, leading officials of the
provincial government and various departments briefed them about
the achievements in implementing China's strategy of speeding up
the development of the western region and development in the
fields of transport, energy and tourism.
</P>
<P>
