<HEADLINE> Biography on Chinese General Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A meeting was held today in
Beijing to celebrate the publication of a biography about Chinese
general Su Yu.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian, member of the Political Bureau and member of the
Secretariat of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, as well as vice chairman of the Central Military
Commission, delivered a speech at the meeting and congratulated
those involved in the publication of the biography.
</P>
<P>
Su Yu, a native of Huidong County, Hunan Province, was born in
1907 and died in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian praised Su Yu's immortal deeds for the liberation
of the Chinese people and his contributions to China's
modernization drive and the building of national defense over the
past half century.
</P>
<P>
He recalled the "glorious" life of Su during his early days and
his contributions during the War of Resistance Against Japanese
Invaders and the War of Liberation.
</P>
<P>
Su directed a series of major campaigns and battles, and was
particularly versed in organizing large formation warfare. Su had
displayed outstanding military skills, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Zhang further noted that during Su's 60 years of revolutionary
life, he showed boundless devotion to the cause of revolution and
worked in the interests of the Party and the people. He adhered to
the Party's disciplines, upheld Party unity.
</P>
<P>
Zhang finally called on the meeting's participants to upheld
the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, unite around the CPC
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and work hard for
the country's modernization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
