<HEADLINE> Manila Says American's Abduction Not to Affect Other Hostages' Release </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government said
Thursday that the kidnapping of American Jeffrey Schilling by the
Abu Sayyaf will not affect the negotiations involving the release
of the remaining six European and one Filipino hostages.
</P>
<P>
According to Press Secretary and Presidential Spokesman Ricardo
Puno, the assurance was given by Abu Sayyaf leader Ghalib Andang,
alias Commander Robot, to chief government negotiator Secretary
Robert Aventajado in their latest talks involving the release of
the Jolo hostages.
</P>
<P>
Puno said Aventajado was also informed by Commander Robot that
his group was in no way involved in the kidnapping of the American
in Zamboanga City on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"Robot assured him (Aventajado) that the American's kidnapping
will not pose an obstacle to the release of the balance of the
hostages being held in Jolo, in accordance with the so-called
global agreement reached to secure their freedom," Puno said.
</P>
<P>
Washington has demanded Schilling's unconditional release and
stressed that the United States does not deal with terrorists.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. embassy belied the Abu Sayyaf's claims that Schilling
was a spy from the Central Intelligence Agency, pointing out that
records show that the 24-year old American was an ordinary
civilian traveling as a tourist.
</P>
<P>
Puno said that according to Aventajado, his office has received
reports that Schilling was married to Ivy Osani, a widow of a
former Abu Sayyaf member, who is a nephew of the group's slain
leader Abdujarak Janjalani.
</P>
<P>
Schilling's wife, according to reports culled by authorities
from the field, is a cousin of Abu Sayyaf leader Abu Sabaya.
</P>
<P>
"Authorities are also verifying reports that Schilling had been
staying in Zamboanga for six months as well as the reasons for his
being there during that period. There were also reports that
Schilling himself had been seeking out the Abu Sayyaf," Puno added.
</P>
<P>
Puno said Aventajado has indicated that he would probably not
get involved this time in the negotiations for Schilling's release.
</P>
<P>
Aventajado, along with former Libyan envoy Rajab Azzarouq,
negotiated the safe release of several Western hostages and
Malaysian nationals kidnapped by the Abu Sayyaf from Sipadan
island, Malaysia almost five months ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
