<HEADLINE> France to Sell Singapore Sea-to-Sea Missiles: Paper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 31 (Xinhua) -- France will sell Singapore sea-to-
sea missiles to equip the frigates it will sell to the Asian
country, La Tribune reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The French company Aerospatiale Matra Missiles will sell these
missiles as part of a package of agreements between Singapore and
French armament groups, the newspaper quoted its sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The missile contract followed an announcement in March by the
Direction des Chantiers Navals that it would sell six Lafayette
frigates to Singapore, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Aerospatiale Matra Missiles has so far refused to confirm
whether the country it has signed the contract with is Singapore
or not.
</P>
<P>
The news was first reported Wednesday by an Israeli newspaper,
the Haaretz. The paper said that Aerospatiale Matra Missiles won a
competition with two Israeli armaments groups in a bid to sell 700
million U.S. dollars worth of sea-to-sea missiles to a "secret
Asian country."
</P>
<P>
The French company, which is affiliated to the European
Aeronautics, Defense and Space group, confirmed that it has won
the contract but refused to reveal the name of the client country.
</P>
