for the Colombian government will not lead the United States into
a combat against the country's leftist guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
-- Whites are no longer the majority in California, the most
populous state in the union, a milestone of profound political and
social impact in a place where ethnic diversity is no longer a
concept but a daily reality.
</P>
<P>
The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The money that the United States uses to fight Western
wildfires will soon exceed 1 billion dollars and Congress may have
to dip into the treasury for the second time this year to pay the
tab.
</P>
<P>
-- A member of the Muslim rebel faction that kidnapped an
American in the southern Philippines this week told a radio
station that the rebels were prepared to talk with the United
States. A U.S. State Department spokesman ruled out negotiations.
</P>
<P>
