<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Sports Drug Agency Releases Testing Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the previous year, the ASDA had found 43 substances in 35
athletes, with 13 in Olympic sports.
</P>
<P>
In the period between 1 July 1999 and June 30 this year, sports
which tested positive included cycling, powerlifting, rugby league,
bodybuilding, athletics, ten pin bowling, archery, karate,
basketball and taekwondo.
</P>
<P>
Substances abused include anabolic agents such as cannabis,
testosterone and stanozolol; diuretics and stimulants such as
pseudoephedrine, amphetamines and caffeine.
</P>
<P>
ASDA Chief Executive Natalie Howson said 6,636 tests had been
conducted in the past 14 months in the most intensive drug testing
program in history of ASDA's 10 year existence.
</P>
</TEXT>
