<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host Powerboat Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will host its very
own Grand Prix, the "Hong Kong Powerboat Grand Prix," around the
Chinese New Year, organizers of the event announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The event, co-organized by the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region government and two other organizations, will be held at
Victoria Harbor on January 28, 2001, the fifth day of the Chinese
new year, with rehearsals on January 27.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's Commissioner for Tourism Mike Rowse said at a press
briefing that the race had the backing of the SAR government and
the support of various departments. He stressed the need to
encourage and create exciting new world events which would
increase visitor arrivals.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong race is the Asia leg and inaugural event of an
international Powerboats World Championship.
</P>
<P>
The global tour will start in Hong Kong before moving to
Melbourne, Australia; west coast of Mexico, Sarasota and New
Jersey in the United States; Toronto, Canada; Cleveland and New
York in the United States; Malta; Greece; and St. Petersburg in
Florida, the United States, for the finale.
</P>
<P>
Twenty top international race teams from the United States,
Europe, Australia, the Middle East and Asia will compete for the "
Hong Kong Powerboat Brand Prix." 
</P>
