<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Upgrades Longest Railway Tunnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Reconstruction on China's
longest Dayaoshan tunnel on the Beijing-Guangzhou railway running
north to south across the country, was completed today after 19
months' hard work.
</P>
<P>
The 14.26-km-long tunnel was built in 1988 in Shaoguan City of
Guangdong Province, south China. However, the complex geological
structure has forced trains to run at a limited speed to ensure
safety.
</P>
<P>
Engineers in charge of the project said that since early 1999,
the local railway department has invested more than 40 million
yuan in upgrading tunnel facilities and the double-track railway
in this section.
</P>
<P>
After using new rail materials and installing advanced alarm
system, trains now travel at a speed of 80 kilometers per hour,
compared with 60 kilometers in the past. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
