<HEADLINE> Chengdu-Kunming Railway Electrified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Electric locomotives will be
running on the Chengdu-Kunming railway in southwest China
beginning September 30 as workers completed the electrification of
the whole on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the Ministry of Railways, the
upgraded railway will allow a highest speed of 85 kilometers per
hour on mountainous areas and its transport ability will double.
</P>
<P>
This has been proved in a one-year trial operation in two
sections of the railway, he added.
</P>
<P>
The electrification of the 30-year-old Chengdu-Kunming railway
began eight years ago at a cost of four billion yuan, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
The 1,100-kilometer-long railway starts at Chengdu, capital of
Sichuan Province, and ends at Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province.
</P>
