<HEADLINE> Russia, Estonia Exchange Expulsion of Diplomats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia on Thursday condemned
Estonia's decision to expel two Russian diplomats for what Tallinn
called activities incompatible with their status, saying it would
evict two Estonian diplomats in response.
</P>
<P>
"Estonia has blamed two Russian diplomats for 'activity not
befitting their status' and proposed that they leave the country
within 48 hours," the Russian Foreign Ministry said in a statement,
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"We bluntly reject the accusations addressed toward the Russian
diplomats as unfounded," the statement said. "It is a deliberate
provocation that seriously damages Russian-Estonian relations.
</P>
<P>
"In response, Russia will expel two Estonian diplomats whose
activity is not befitting their diplomatic status within 48 hours.
The Estonian ambassador was summoned to the Russian Foreign
Ministry and informed of this today."
</P>
<P>
The identities of the diplomats involved have not been
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Moscow said it regretted that "the recent positive dynamics of
bilateral relations is being sacrificed to the ambitions of the
Estonian secret services," the statement said. "Estonia bears the
full responsibility for this." 
</P>
</TEXT>
