<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Mixed on Thursday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond market ended
mixed as the weak domestic stocks represented a boost for bonds
while several new stock subscriptions and placements tightened the
money supply. Transaction value expanded by 196 million yuan to 1.
85 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Of the six current treasuries on the market, two slipped by 0.
11 percent on average, two advanced no more than 0.04 percent and
two stayed unchanged, according to Homeway, China's leading on-
line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009908 shed 0.14 percent to close at 102.99 yuan, driving
the yield up 0.03 percentage points to 3.32 percent. Meanwhile,
the turnover on the bond swelled to 663 million yuan, versus the
313 million yuan on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009704 tumbled another 0.08 percent below its ten-day
average price to 145.61 yuan, so the bond will probably dip
further under the pressure from the ten-day average. Its yield
picked up 0.02 percentage points to 3.84 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bond 009905 closed the session up 0.02 percent and the mew
floating-rate 010004, whose coupon rate is 2.87 percent this year,
paced up 0.04 percent to 104.85 yuan.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market saw a tame boom, fueled by the stock
subscriptions and placements. Trade volume of three-day, seven-day,
14-day and 28-day repurchasing transactions totaled 5.77 billion
yuan, up 2.45 folds from Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Most of the repurchasing interest rates rallied. The interest
rate of the three-day repurchasing agreement gained 0.69
percentage points to 4.49 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
