<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-Share Market Records Biggest Tumble in Four Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
plunged 17.72 points, or 2.79 percent, to 617.42 points on
Thursday, while the sub-index ended at 4,881.05 points, down 2.12
percent from its previous close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 14.53 billion yuan (1.75 billion US dollars),
which was 12.20 percent more than Wednesday's total.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Shenzhen Composite Index, seeing the largest one-
day tumble since March 16th, nose-dived to hit its lowest level in
one month and a week, according to Homeway, China's leading on-
line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
An extreme lack of investor confidence, hurt by gloomy
corporate profit outlook, was the major reason triggering an all-
around sell-off. Market players could hardly see any positive
signs from the fact that one in ten Chinese listed companies
reported losses for the first six months ended June 2000 to end
the half-year earnings season today.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmingly beat gainers by 523 to 35, with 12
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Chenzhen Universe Industrial Stock Co., Ltd. bucked the main
trend, advancing 9.97 percent to 17.31 yuan as the market
bellwether.
</P>
<P>
Jiujiang Chemical Fiber Co., Ltd., the biggest loser, dropped 7.
03 percent to 15.73 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Analysts note that the market is expected to be on the volatile
side, as direction seems vague ahead amid vulnerable sentiment.
Investors will be watching the fundamentals that are critical in
shaping the near-term outlook.  
</P>
</TEXT>
