<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Israeli Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Israeli newspapers on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Post:
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Foreign Ministry officials believe Palestinian
National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat will not unilaterally
declare a Palestinian state on September 13, a ministry official
said.
</P>
<P>
The official said the Palestinians are likely to delay the date
for two months, to November 15, the anniversary of the Palestine
Liberation Organization (PLO) declaration of independence in the
West Bank, Gaza, and east Jerusalem, issued in Algiers in 1988.
</P>
<P>
