<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Soeharto's Trial Adjourned to Mid-September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Owing to the absence of the
defendant in the court, the South Jakarta District Court finally
had to adjourn on Thursday the trial process against former
Indonesian President Soeharto to September 14.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto was absent from Thursday morning's hearing on his
corruption case, according to a medical team report which was read
out by Soeharto's lawyers in the court room, due to his bad health
condition.
</P>
<P>
Chief Judge Lalu Mariyun said the trial will be resumed again
at 10:00 a.m. (local time) on September 14, at the Ministry of
Agriculture building to hear reports from Soeharto's medical team
on the condition of the former ruler.
</P>
<P>
The first trial of Soeharto was opened on Thursday morning at
about 10:00 a.m. (local time) at the Ministry of Agriculture
building. The trial only lasted around one hour, with 10 minutes
of suspension.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's hearing was dominated by reports on the 79-year-old
man's health condition delivered by his lawyers.
</P>
<P>
The report, issued by Soeharto's doctor team, said the former
president who ran the country with an iron hand for more than
three decades was still not in a good shape to appear before the
court for questioning.
</P>
<P>
"Soeharto's nervous system is still obstructed due to a series
of stroke attacks," the medical report read out by Mohamad Assegaf,
one of Soeharto's lawyers, said.
</P>
<P>
It also said Soeharto has a big problem in his communication
skills as well as his memory system.
</P>
<P>
"And his kidney also has been suffering from a mild disturbance,
" the report said, adding that the blood pressure of the former
president has also risen.
</P>
<P>
Responding to the medical report, chief prosecuting attorney
Muchtar Arifin then asked the presiding judge to set up an
independent doctor team to examine the former president's health
condition and then release what he said will be "a second opinion
on the health condition of Soeharto."
</P>
<P>
"The setting up of the independent doctor team is intended to
get an independent opinion on the health condition of the
defendant. It will be fair if such a thing is considered (to be
realized)," Arifin said.
</P>
<P>
But chief judge Mariyun has not yet decided whether the court
will meet the prosecuting attorney's demand for the establishment
of the independent medical team.
</P>
<P>
Generally, the first day of Soeharto's hearing ran smoothly
with no clashes reported.
</P>
<P>
Some student groups staged a rally supporting the trial process
against "the smiling general" who is alleged to have misused some
500 million U.S. dollars of public funds in the seven tax-free
foundations he chaired when he was in power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
