<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo For Third Straight Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed lower in Tokyo
for the third consecutive day Thursday as investors continued to
take profits following the recent sharp gains in share prices.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange fell 40.41 points, or 0.24
percent from Wednesday's close to end at 16,861.26.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all First
Section issues, dropped 7.41 points or 0.49 percent to 1,511.44.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 589.99 million
shares from Wednesday's 523.04 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
The textile, rubber and retail sectors marked sharp declines,
while gainers included the brokerage, wholesale and oil sectors.
</P>
<P>
High-priced information technology issues were mixed.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 791 to 445, with 163 issues closing unchanged. 
