<HEADLINE> China to Hold Crystal Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth China Donghai Crystal
Festival is scheduled for September 28-30 in Donghai, a coastal
county in Jiangsu Province, east China.
</P>
<P>
Displays of domestic and foreign crystal products as well as
trade and investment talks are to be held during the three-day
festival.
</P>
<P>
Crystal producers and dealers from France, the Netherlands,
Germany, Japan and several other countries will participate in the
event, according to festival organizers.
</P>
<P>
Donghai's reserves of crystals and quartz accounts for more
than half of the country's total. The county government has
decided to build a national research, development and processing
center with global market appeal.
</P>
<P>
The county now has hundreds of firms engaged in mining,
production and processing.
</P>
<P>
Business people from countries such as Germany, France, and
Japan have also been engaged in crystal processing in the county.
</P>
<P>
The biennial festival was initiated in 1990 and has since
attracted an increasing number of crystal traders and handicraft
fans from around the world.  
