<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese, ROK Military Officers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the general
staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), held talks
with Cho Yungkil, chairman of the joint chiefs of staff of the
Republic of Korea (ROK)'s armed forces.
</P>
<P>
They exchanged views on issues in bilateral relations and
regional and international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, Fu stressed that the PLA will faithfully
carry out the task endowed by the Communist Party of China and the
Chinese people and resolutely oppose conspiracy of any form aimed
at separate the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He added that the PLA, in line with the principle of "peaceful
reunification and one country, two systems," will continue to make
efforts for an early settlement of the Taiwan issue and realize
the full reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Cho said that he hopes the two countries and their armed forces
will continuously enrich and develop their friendly cooperation
within the framework of the ROK-China relations of partnership of
cooperation geared to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the two countries will join
efforts to contribute to maintaining regional stability and
development.
</P>
<P>
Cho arrived in China on Monday for an official goodwill visit
at the invitation of Fu. 
</P>
