<HEADLINE> China Did Not Import Plasma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- China has an adequate supply of
plasma for clinic use and does not need to import any plasma from
foreign countries, today's Beijing Youth Daily cited an official
source as saying.
</P>
<P>
A newspaper recently reported that plasma polluted by HIV and
hepatitis virus had been transferred from an African country to a
number of countries in the past 20 years, including China.
</P>
<P>
