<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmer Launches Website </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Miao Jianchun, a fisherman in
north China's Tianjin Municipality, recently launched a website
providing e-commerce services as well as free information about
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
So far more than 500 on-line deals worth over 15 million yuan (
about 1.8 million U.S. dollars) have been reportedly made through
his website.
</P>
<P>
"Surfing the Internet profits much more than with the fishing
net," Miao said.
</P>
<P>
Miao is not the only Chinese farmer who has turned to the Net
or benefited from it.
</P>
<P>
According to a latest survey, an increasing number of Chinese
farmers are taking to the Internet, some even organized overseas
companies via the Net.
</P>
<P>
There are 1500 agricultural websites in China.
</P>
<P>
"The Internet is changing the life of Chinese farmers as
greatly as that the TV once did," a local expert said. 
</P>
