<HEADLINE> Anti-Corruption Movie Hits Box-Office Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese movie "Live or Die",
with an anti-corruption theme, has earned record high box office
takings in Beijing, according to today's Beijing Youth Daily.
</P>
<P>
The movie created 1.05 million yuan (about 125,000 U.S. dollars)
at the box office on the first day of release, and 1.1 million
yuan on the next day, a record of single day box-office earnings
in Beijing, the newspaper report said.
</P>
<P>
"So far, more than 400,000 audiences have watched the movie
which has been screened nearly 1,000 times," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The movie's original script, a novel titled "Option", has also
seen a comeback with brisk sales in the nation's capital.
</P>
<P>
The publisher said that more than 100,000 copies of the novel
have been printed. 
</P>
