<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Traditional Medicine Help Cure Wild Animals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Yunnan Baiyao" and "Yunnan Hongyao" are among the most
applicable and effective Chinese traditional medicine applied to
the wounds of the wild animals, said Zheng Xiaohong, an expert on
wildlife in this park.
</P>
<P>
A lion cub got back on its feet after a week after taking the "
Yunnan Hongyao". This medicine also cured a zebra's badly hurt
back foot after three weeks.
</P>
<P>
"The Yunnan Hongyao can effectively stop bleeding, promote
blood circulation and remove blood stasis," Zheng said.
</P>
<P>
"Moreover, it is very cheap," the expert added. There are about
6,000 wildlife in the park covering an area of over 300 hectares.
</P>
