<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on The Move (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The development of the western part of China should be carried
out under the unified plans of the central leadership, while
bringing into consideration the local social and economic
situation.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Li Lanqing made the remark during his inspection
tour of Golmud, northwest China's Qinghai Province, on August 27.
During his stay, Li visited several local schools.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with local officials, Li, who is also a member of
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee, urged the western region to
develop science, technology and education sectors.
</P>
<P>
Western China is meeting rare historic opportunities and local
governments should take a new road of development compatible to
the system of the socialist market economy and the era of
knowledge-based economy, said the vice premier.
</P>
<P>
 Xi'an to Host Investment, Trade Fair
</P>
<P>
The China Xi'an Investment and Trade Fair will be held from
October 3-8 this year in this capital of northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
Cui Lintao, secretary of the Xi'an City Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party, said at a news briefing on August 23
that Xi'an will offer more than 200 projects to both domestic and
overseas investors attending the fair.
</P>
<P>
These projects mainly cover the construction of infrastructure
facilities, tourism facilities, and development of machinery, e-
information, bio-medicine, building materials, food, real estate
and modern agriculture. An exhibition displaying quality products
from Chinese and overseas firms will be held simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that a great number of Chinese and overseas
business people have signed up for the upcoming event, which is
sponsored by the Xi'an city government with the help of the German
city of Dortmund, the Japan-China Association on Economy and Trade,
and the Hong Kong Trade Development Council.  
</P>
