<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Build 310 Geoparks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 31 (Xinhua) -- China is planning to build 310
geological parks in the next 10 years to protect its natural sites,
according to today's People's Daily.
</P>
<P>
China will also try to put five to eight of the geoparks into
the world geo-heritage list.
</P>
<P>
To fulfill these goals, China has recently set up the Geopark
Protection Office and the Geopark Evaluation Committee, the paper
said.
</P>
<P>
Non-renewable natural resources provide geo-heritage with
scientific and sight-seeing value and insight into the study of
the planet's evolution.
</P>
<P>
Despite much headway made in the protection of natural sites,
China has still yet to finish the national survey of its geo-
heritage, delaying urgent protection of the sites, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Under the protection plan drafted by the Ministry of Land and
Resources, effective measures will be taken to halt the damages to
the natural sites. A national heritage protection system will be
established in the next 10 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
