<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President Appoints Committee on National Pension  Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has appointed a committee to make recommendations for
a national policy on pensions including a pension scheme and a
welfare package for government pensioners.
</P>
<P>
The Presidential Secretariat said in a press release on
Thursday that the committee headed by senior administrator P.A.
Senaratne is expected to present its report by February 28, 2001.
</P>
<P>
Under its terms of reference the committee will examine
discrepancies and anomalies that have risen from computations and
revisions of pensions implemented from time to time with a view to
rectifying them.
</P>
<P>
The committee is expected to recommend action to prevent delays
in the payment of pensions and the benefits of the widows and
orphans pension scheme. It will also craft a social security
scheme for pensioners to provide them with medical care, housing
and recreational facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
