<HEADLINE> China, France Should View Relations From Strategic Viewpoint: Legislator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 30 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Li Peng
said here Wednesday that China and France should view their
relations from a strategic point of view and value their existing
friendship.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark during a meeting with Raymond Forni,
president of the National Assembly of France. Both Li and Forni
are here attending the Millennium Conference of Presiding Officers
of National Parliaments, which began here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress of China, said that to push forward for a more healthy
and steady development of China-France relations will serve the
fundamental interests of the two countries as well as peace and
stability of the entire world.
</P>
<P>
Both China and France should view their relations from a
strategic angle and cherish their friendship, Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
Forni said France attaches great importance to both its
relations with China and the relations between China and the
European Union. He added that France hopes to further expand its
cooperative relations with China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
