<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Seaside Resort Combats Water Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINHUANGDAO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- All of the polluted water in
Beidaihe, one of China's most famous summer resorts, has been
disposed of and cleaned before flowing into the sea, an official
source said.
</P>
<P>
The quality of sea water there has been significantly improved
this summer and has met the requirements of the state's first-
class sea water standard, according to the local environment
monitoring center.
</P>
<P>
Last year the local government invested 120 million yuan (15
million U.S. dollars) on a sewage-disposal factory which started
operation earlier this summer. The government also launched a
drive to clean the rubbish so as to protect the ocean from being
polluted.
</P>
<P>
Also, most of the 1,188 local enterprises have met the waste-
discharging requirements, which has helped clean the sea water.
</P>
<P>
Covering a land area of 70 square kilometers along the Bohai
Sea, Beidaihe attracts over 2 million tourists every year.
</P>
</TEXT>
