<HEADLINE> Indonesian Local Court Prepares to Try Soehart Thursday Morning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Amid increasing worry about
Indonesian former President Soeharto's court appearance on
Thursday, three cars left Soeharto's home in central Jakarta at 8:
25 in the morning, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
But, it was not clear whether Soeharto was among the passengers
in the cars and where they will go.
</P>
<P>
A witness said he saw one of Soeharto's lawyers in the first
car.
</P>
<P>
According to schedule, at about 10:00 local time the South
Jakarta District Court will try Soeharto on the charges of
corruption.
</P>
<P>
However, there was uncertainty ahead of the long-awaited trial
following an explosion late on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
A parked yellow city bus exploded in front of the Mitra Karya
auto repair shop on JL. Taman Marge satwa, South Jakarta, about
300 meters across the street from the Ministry of Agriculture
compound, where the trial will be held. No casualties were
reported and there was also little damage to surrounding buildings.
</P>
<P>
Rumors have been spreading that the 79-year-old man may be
absent as his health condition is not good.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Soeharto's lawyer Mohammad Assegaf said his
client would undergo a medical checkup Thursday morning to make
sure he is okay to appear before the court.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto, who ruled the country for 32 years, is alleged to
have misused some 580 million U.S. dollars of public funds in the
seven charitable foundations he chaired. 
</P>
</TEXT>
