<HEADLINE> Stranded Whale in Macao Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A young humpback whale, which was
stranded in the shallow waters of Macao Wednesday, has died.
</P>
<P>
Specialists in Hong Kong are scheduled to come Thursday
afternoon and help dissect the 11.8-meter-long whale baby whale.
</P>
<P>
The whale was found by a local marine police at 3:05 p.m.
Wednesday, when the sea was at ebb tide. People with the Macao
Port Authority, marine police and local fishermen rushed to the
site for rescue work.
</P>
<P>
The rescue was rather difficult for the whale was stranded in
the shallow water only about 30 cm deep. As hours passed, the
whale failed to survive in the rising tide.
</P>
<P>
Local fishermen said they had never seen whales in the waters
around Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
