<HEADLINE> Mongolia Suffers More Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 31 (Xinhua) -- An official report reveals
that 167 steppe and forest fires broke out in the Mongolian
countryside in the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the report released by the Mongolian State Board
on Fighting Fires, the number of fires in the first half of this
year went up 28 percent compared with the same period of last year,
with an economic loss reaching more than 400,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the fires, 1.2 million hectares of forest and 3.
8 million hectares of pasture have been burned; 300 head of
livestock were also killed.
</P>
<P>
The report says that most of the fires were caused by
carelessness. 
</P>
