<HEADLINE> Bosnia Supports "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Bosnia sticks to "One China"
policy, reaffirmed Bosnian leaders Wednesday in Sarajevo when
meeting a visiting Chinese delegation.
</P>
<P>
During their talks with Liu Guchang, assistant to the Chinese
foreign minister, Zivko Radisic and Spasoj Tusefljak, member of
Bosnian Presidency and prime minister of Bosnian Government
separately, said that Bosnia will carry out what Bosnia has
promised in the Bosnian-Chinese joint communique on the
establishment of diplomatic relations and will never maintain any
kinds of official relations or conduct any kinds of official
contacts with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The two Bosnian leaders said that they both admired what China
has achieved in politics, economy and in other fields in recent
years. "China is playing an increasingly vital role in
international affairs," they said.
</P>
<P>
Liu elaborated on the Chinese government's policies during the
talks. "China supports Bosnia's independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity and respects Bosnia's political system on
the basis of democratic consultation among the three ethnic groups
of the Moslems, Croats and Serbs.
</P>
<P>
"It is China's established policy to strengthen friendly
exchanges with Bosnia and develop the Chinese-Bosnian cooperation
in all fields," Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation headed by Liu arrived in Sarajevo
Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
