<HEADLINE> Austrian President Urges End to EU Sanctions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Austrian President Thomas Klestil
Wednesday urged the EU to lift its sanctions against the Austrian
government, which currently includes members of the far-right
Freedom Party.
</P>
<P>
Austria's EU partners imposed sanctions on Austria after the
far-right Freedom Party joined a coalition government with the
conservative People's Party in February.
</P>
<P>
"I hope the 14 (EU) countries lift the unjust measures taken
against the Austrian government as soon as possible," Klestil said
at the opening ceremony of an agricultural exposition in the State
of Upper Wels, Austria.
</P>
<P>
The president said he has tried in the past at various times
to persuade Austria's EU partners to ease sanctions against his
country. He will also attend the U.N. Millennium Summit next week
to try and end Austria's isolation by EU, Klestil said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the three-person expert panel currently
working in Austria sent by EU will probably take the first steps
to break the impasse between Austria and EU.
</P>
<P>
The panel, led by former Finnish president Martti Ahtisaari,
began on July 28 to evaluate Austria's political situation. The 14
EU countries will decide whether to lift its sanctions according
to a final report by the panel. 
</P>
