<HEADLINE> Panama Reinforces Border With Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 30 (Xinhua) -- Panama is reinforcing its
border with Colombia to prevent a tide of Colombians that may be
displaced after the implementation of the "Plan Colombia."
</P>
<P>
Panamanian Minister of the Interior and Justice Winston
Spadafora said Wednesday that the National Office for the
Attention to Refugees is ready for a possible movement of
Colombians to Panama.
</P>
<P>
At the ceremony of the Operations Center for Emergencies where
Central American civil protection personnel will be trained,
Spadafora said, "Necessary measures are being implemented for
possible repercussions from the Plan Colombia in Panama."
</P>
<P>
He said that some National Air Service helicopters are being
refurbished for the protection of the border with Colombia.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that whatever happens in Colombia, " There will be
a risk for Panama and the other neighboring countries," saying
that if needed, more troops could be sent to Darien, the province,
some 300 kilometers east of the Panamanian capital, bordering
Colombia.  
</P>
