<HEADLINE> Longo Sets European Record in 600 Meters Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 30 (Xinhua) -- With 16 day to go before the Sydney
Olympics, Italy's Andrea Longo show his restored form when he set
an European record over the unusual 600-meter race at the Oak
track Meet Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian runner completed the distance in one minute, 14.41
seconds, improving by 0.31 the previous European mark set by Andre
Bucher of Switzerland last year.
</P>
<P>
In other events of the rain-marred meet in this north Italian
city, Jeff Laynes of the United States won the 100 meters in 10.27
seconds, edging compatriot Tim Harden (10.30) and Italian veteran
Stefano Tilli (10.33).
</P>
<P>
Paul Korir of Kenya took the 800-meter in 1:45.20, ahead of
Brazilian Osmar Dos Santos.
</P>
<P>
Jamaican sprinters swept the three top places in the women's
200-meter race. Beverly McDonald won in 22.69 seconds, ahead of
Juliet Campbell and Marlene Frazer. 
