<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strange Slopes Found in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, August 31 (Xinhua)-- Seven strange slopes were
discovered recently in Yanggao County, Datong City in north China'
s Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Without any power supply, automobiles could run up the slope at
the speed of 30 kilometers per hour. Water flows to the top of the
slope in the same fashion. People also feel hindered while riding
bicycles down the slope.
</P>
<P>
The slopes, each from 40 meters to 100 meters long, are part of
a mountain path between two villages of the Yanggao County. The
average elevation of the slopes is approximately 20 degrees.
</P>
<P>
The slopes in Datong city are not the only mysterious slopes in
China. The "strange slope", found in 1990 in Shenyang, capital of
northeast China's Liaoning Province, is more widely known.
</P>
<P>
Drivers have to accelerate when driving down the 80-meter-long
slope and drive upward with the brakes on, otherwise the vehicle
will accelerate on its own.
</P>
<P>
In the past decade, more than four million tourists including
over 50,000 from abroad have visited the strange slope in Shenyang.
The latest discovery of the seven slopes is expected to attract
more visitors to Datong, China's major coal production base.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
