<HEADLINE> Tanjug Director Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 30 (Xinhua)-- Dusan Djordjevic, director and
editor-in-chief of the Yugoslav news agency Tanjug, died Wednesday
here after a long illness.
</P>
<P>
Djordjevic, born in 1945, graduated from the College of
Economics and worked for Radio Belgrade, the Privredni Pregled
publishing house, Tanjug and the Yugoslav Ministry of Information.
</P>
<P>
Djordjevic headed Tanjug since 1998, including the difficult
period between March and June 1999, when NATO launched an aerial
bombardment on Yugoslavia's Serbian forces over Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Last year, he received the life achievement award from the
Serbian Association of Journalists.  
</P>
