<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Refuses to Accept Its Soldier's Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The Indian Military
authorities have refused to accept the body of an Indian soldier
from the Pakistani side, the spokesman of the Pakistani Inter
Services Public Relations said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Indian soldier was killed when Pakistani Army repulsed an
Indian attack on one of its forward posts on the Line of Control (
LoC) in Rawalakot Sector, Kashmir, on the night between August 23/
24 and it was recovered by a Pakistan Army Patrol on the LoC, four
days later, under heavy Indian automatic and artillery fire in a
difficult terrain.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question, the spokesman stated that the
refusal to accept the body of its own soldier was utter disregard
to the martial tradition. Apparent reason for this refusal and
insensitivity towards their fallen soldiers was due to the fact
that the Indians had been denying attack on the Pakistani Post and
acceptance of the body would expose them to the world as having
attacked and failed in their bid to capture it.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has unilaterally offered cease-fire and a safe passage
to the Indian troops or the recovery of other bodies lying in the
area. These Indian soldiers were killed while retreating after the
same unsuccessful attack on the night of August 23/24. However,
The Indian military authorities have not yet responded to the
offer despite reiteration of this offer from the Pakistani side,
the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
