<HEADLINE> Athens Olympic Village to be Ready by 2004 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 30 (Xinhua) -- The Athens Olympic Village,
designed to have 8,800 bedrooms, would be ready by February 2004,
Greece's Deputy Labor Minister Christos Protopappas said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Protopappas said that work would begin in the first quarter of
2001 and the 2,500 housing units would be ready within the
timetable set in the contract signed by the Worker's Housing
Organization and the Athens 2004 Olympics Organizing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Describing as huge the Athens Olympic Village construction
project, the minister said that it would be equal to those built
in Atlanta, U.S. and Sydney, Australia.
</P>
<P>
The Athens Olympic Village with a total accommodation area of 1,
240,000 square meters will be created in the Lekanes region of
Aharnai, and will accommodate the sixteen thousand men and women
athletes and accompanying persons who are to take part in the 2004
Games. 
</P>
