<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops Routing Switch Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 31 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese company in western
Sichuan Province made major breakthroughs in developing routing
switch products, the most essential equipment in internet
technology.
</P>
<P>
Proved to be on par with international standards, this Chinese-
made products is expected to pose a challenge to the U.S.-based
Sisco which currently holds monopoly of China's routing switch
market.
</P>
<P>
Maipu Information Technology Group, based in the capital city
of Chengdu, told reporters that it will realize the
industrialization of routing switch production and compete with
Sisco in three to five years.
</P>
<P>
So far, Maipu's routing switches were already successfully
applied to some financial, public security and postal departments
in China.
</P>
<P>
Maipu company was the first modem producer in China.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the home-made routing switch products are much
cheaper and has great significance in protecting China's network
information security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
