<HEADLINE> Large Stone Forest Found In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The stone forest is located in Taiyanghe Township, Shi'en of
Hubei Province. It occupies a total land area of about 10 square
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
All the stones are grotesque in shape, and some look like
flying dragons and angry tigers, while others look like blooming
flowers, a local source said.
</P>
<P>
The source said that the best thing for the stones is that they
are in the middle of a real forest and the "trees, grasses and
flowers make the stones even more beautiful."
</P>
