<HEADLINE> Cuba Confirms Detaining 3 Swedish Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban government confirmed
Thursday the detention of three alleged Swedish journalists
because they "promoted subversive acts" and violated Cuba's
internal laws.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference, Cuban Foreign Minister Felipe Perez
Roque said the Swedes carried out illegal acts to contribute to "
desperate attempts organized in the United States to promote
internal subversion."
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister emphasized that Cuba will defend its right
to uphold internal security and stability and will prevent trouble-
makers and hired agents invading Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Swedish citizens Birger Thuresson, Peter Geoetell and Helena
Soederquist came to Cuba as tourists last Thursday and were
stopped Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"These three people have been arrested by way of warning as is
done in any country wherever the laws of the country are broken,"
the top Cuban diplomat said, adding that the Swedes have been
cleared to leave Cuba Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sweden Wednesday formally protested against the arrests to the
Cuban deputy foreign minister, who was on a visit to Norway, it
was reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
