<HEADLINE> U.S., Cuba to Resume Talks on Migration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON,August 31 (Xinhua) -- Cuba has agreed to resume
suspended talks on migration with the United States, the State
Department said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The Cubans have informed us that they are now prepared to
resume these immigration talks," said State Department spokesman
Richard Boucher.
</P>
<P>
Boucher said that Cuba's decision to restart the talks,
suspended three months ago, was conveyed to Washington in a 15-
page diplomatic note delivered to the State Department late
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The talks, which have been held twice a year since the
migration agreement was concluded in 1994, were to take place in
late June. But Boucher said a new date and venue for the talks had
not yet been decided. 
</P>
