<HEADLINE> London, Frankfurt Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The London stock market ended its
five-month high Thursday as tech, media and telecom stocks soared.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark index FTSE 100 surged 57.6 points or 0.87 percent
to 6,672.7, its highest finish since March 27.
</P>
<P>
Chip designer ARM rocketed 10.1 percent, fiber-optic component
maker BHM added 7.1 percent and Internet service provider
Freeserve rose almost 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among media shares, shares of cable company Telewest
Communications soared 15.1 percent, Pearson rose 6.4 percent and
United News &AMP; Media jumped 5.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The pan-European FTSE Eurotop 300 rose 0.7 percent to 1,669.95,
with its computer services component rising 3.3 percent and its
information technology hardware sub-index up 3.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, stock markets shrugged off the ECB's latest
interest rate increase as technology shares stormed higher with
Epcos AG gaining near 7 percent.
</P>
<P>
But the CAC 40 in Paris closed down 9.2 points, or 0.1 percent,
to 6,625.42. 
</P>
</TEXT>
